<!DOCTYPE html>

<html>
 <head>
  <title>HTTP 500 - Review Board is taking a nap</title>
  <meta http-equiv="refresh" content="60" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1" />
  <style>
   body {
     background-color: #222950;
     color: #DDD;
     font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif;
     font-size: 8pt;
     text-align: center;
     padding: 10em 2em;
   }

   h1 {
     color: white;
     font-size: 250%;
     font-weight: normal;
   }

   img {
     float: left;
     margin-right: 3em;
   }

   p {
    text-align: justify;
    font-size: 160%;
   }

   #explanation {
     display: inline-block;
     max-width: 50em;
     overflow-y: hidden;
     padding-top: 4em;
     text-align: left;
   }

   #wrapper {
    display: inline-block;
    text-align: center;
   }

   @media screen and (max-width: 720px),
          screen and (max-device-width: 720px) and (orientation: landscape) {
     body {
       padding: 2em;
     }

     img {
       float: none;
       margin-right: 0;
       text-align: center;
       max-width: 75%;
       height: auto;
     }

     p {
       text-align: left;
     }

     #explanation {
       padding-top: 2em;
     }
   }
  </style>
 </head>
 <body>
  <div id="wrapper">
   <img src="@siteroot_noslash@/static/rb/images/500/zzz.png"
        srcset="@siteroot_noslash@/static/rb/images/500/zzz@2x.png 1x
                @siteroot_noslash@/static/rb/images/500/zzz@2x.png 2x"
        width="296" height="254" alt="" />

   <div id="explanation">
    <h1>Shhh... Review Board is taking a nap.</h1>
    <p>
     You hit a HTTP 500 error, which means something might be wrong.
     If this is a temporary outage, Review Board should wake up soon.
    </p>
    <p>
     Or maybe you've found a bug. If so, good job! Please report it to your
     admins. They'll be able to help you out.
    </p>
   </div>
  </div>
 </body>
</html>
